        <Parent_String>cornets (aerophones) [300042314], lip-vibrated aerophones with conical bore: with valves [300209198], lip-vibrated aerophones with conical bore [300195078], lip-vibrated aerophones [300041639], aerophones [300041622], sound devices by acoustical characteristics [300041621], sound devices (equipment) [300387677], Sound Devices (hierarchy name) [300041619], Furnishings and Equipment (hierarchy name) [300264551], Objects Facet [300264092]</Parent_String>
        <Hier_Rel_Type>Genus/Species-BTG</Hier_Rel_Type>
      </Preferred_Parent>
    </Parent_Relationships>
    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Valved brass instruments of the cornet family of alto range, usually pitched at E flat or F, having a conical bore and medium-sized bell; the tube, about 79 inches in length, can be coiled in tuba, orchestral trumpet, or helicon shape.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instrumentos de válvulas de bronce de la familia de las cornetas de registro alto, generalmente en tono de Mi bemol o Fa, con un diámetro interior cónico y campana de tamaño mediano; el tubo, de aproximadamente de 79 pulgadas de longitud, puede estar enrrollado en forma de tuba, trompeta orquestal o helicón.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Koperblaasinstrumenten met kleppen behorend tot de kornetfamilie, met een altbereik; met conische boring, middelgrote klankbeker en een ongeveer twee meter lange buis, gedraaid in de vorm van een tuba, orkestrale trompet of helikon. De grondtoon is meestal Es of F.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052452/Encyclopedie van muziekinstrumenten (1977)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>活栓型黃銅製管樂器，是屬於中音部音域範圍的短號家族的樂器，通常是降E調或者是F調，有著一道圓錐型口徑和一個中型的喇叭口；長度大約為79英吋，能夠盤繞成大號/低音兼次中音大號、交響樂小號，或者是低音大號(helicon)的形狀。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052784/TELDAP database (2009-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mit Klappen versehenes Blechblasinstrument der Kornettfamilie in Alt-Lage, gewöhnlich gestimmt in Es oder F, mit konischer Bohrung und mittelgroßem Schalltrichter; die Röhre, etwa 2 Meter lang, kann in Form einer Tuba, einer Orchestertrompete oder eines Helikon gewunden sein.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000122134/IfM Berlin</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instrumentos de latão valvulados da família dos cornetes de alcance alto, geralmente afinados em mi bemol ou fá, com furo cônico e sino de tamanho médio; o tubo, com cerca de 79 polegadas de comprimento, pode ser enrolado em forma de tuba, trompete orquestral ou helicon.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000316/CVAA-BR</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
